Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat
oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Carefully prick @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} all over with a #fork{}. Place in
a medium #microwave-safe bowl{}; cover tightly with #plastic wrap{} and
microwave until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. (You'll roast the potatoes in Step 3.)

Meanwhile, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Finely chop
@chives{1/4%ounce}.

Pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season generously all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest for at least
~{5%minutes}. Wash and dry pan.

Add @truffle seasoning{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4 servings), a drizzle of
@cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{} to bowl with potatoes; toss to combine.

> Feel free to add more truffle seasoning if you like!

Transfer potatoes to an oiled #baking sheet{} and spread out in an even layer.
Use a #potato masher{} to smash potatoes until they are 1/2 inch thick.

Roast on top rack for ~{8%minutes}.

Once potatoes have roasted 8 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Carefully
flip potatoes and push to one side of baking sheet; toss green beans on
opposite side with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until potatoes are crispy and green beans are browned and
tender, ~{10-12%minutes}. (For 4 servings, flip potatoes and return to top rack;
toss green beans on a second #baking sheet{} and roast on middle rack.)

Meanwhile, combine chives, @cream sauce base{4%ounce}, and
@Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} in pan used for steak over medium heat. Bring
to a low simmer and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is smooth and slightly
thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Thinly slice steak against the grain.

Divide steak, smashed potatoes, and green beans between plates in separate
sections. Serve chive sauce on the side for dipping.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.